      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That \"symbolic representation\" thing is exactly what I'm getting at, but I think it goes way deeper than just \"national unity.\" It feels almost... ritualistic? Like, if you look at the specific angles of the spokes from the monument, they aren't just lines on a map, they feel like they're designed to direct something. Not just ideas, but actual energy or something. Do you think the geometry could be used to influence the collective mood or psyche of the people living there?",
